review_blob: Advertised on the bottle as a Triple IPA but does not have the hop-hit of most DIPAs. Still tasty stuff, masks its extreme ABV percentage well and has a pleasing aftertaste to boot. In this instance a bottled bomber lives up to the bomber moniker. One in the glass and another in the fridge will keep one warm on a rainy winter desert night.

Bitter beyond DIPA norms but balanced just about beyond anything else in its class. Brings the same notes that Left Coast Hop Juice has, but not as harsh on the alky aftertaste with actually higher ABV. Hope they keep this one coming from the vats. DO NOT consume too many too fast.
Man, you sure hate to slam a talented dead guys recipe but this is not the ususal quality offering from Stone. Still an overall interesting brew albeit a little sweet with an unusual aftertaste.
beer_name: Stone Matts Burning Rosids Imperial Cherry Wood Smoked Saison

review_blob: One full tick up from the unbelievable regular Stone IPA. This is one we should hope they keep in long term production.

Good overall appearace out of the bottle. Syrupy smooth and sweet with high yeast taste. Alcohol is ever present when sipping this concotion. Finish one 22 bomber and you will know why the alky is in the taste.
beer_name: Left Coast Asylum Belgian-Style Tripel Ale

review_blob: Very impressive CA microbrew.  Lives up to its DIPA label.  Citrus and hops abound and after just one 22 ozr you will realize the potency of this elixir.  Destined to try this liquid again for sure
Good PacNW microbrew IPA.  Not as citrus as expected for this style beer.  Aftertaste left the best impression.  Would buy this one again.
Excellent Bottled microbrew bought locally here at a LV liquor store.  Surprising aftertase of grapefruit that lingers.
